Articles.Content:
So this is a weird problem, and it's causing me problems on what I'm trying to accomplish. I searched but couldn't find a fix.

I need to dock two of my ships, but one of them has a weird reaction wheel that's stuck about 5m out in front of the dock, from where a previous piece used to be. It somehow got stuck to this ship when the original piece was undocked, instead of going with the original piece (an MPL).

Now I can't dock, because I bump into this piece and can't get past it. If I was really good, I do have a docking port on the side of the other ship, but I can't seem to sneak it in between.

I have KAS and KIS. Can I do an EVA to remove it? I guess I'd need a wrench with me (which I don't have at the moment). One ship is a probe, one is piloted. I can send a third ship if I need to, or just a new ship I guess and send this one back to land on Kerbin (hopefully this piece doesn't cause problems landing).

Is there a way to fix this with some cheat edit menu or something?

You can see the reaction wheel in between the two ships, it's a part of the ship on the right.

You could probably blow it up by using the object thrower in the F12 cheat menu.

Save first, though, just in case that part is somehow actually in the middle of the ship.

10 minutes ago, Geonovast said:

You could probably blow it up by using the object thrower in the F12 cheat menu.

Save first, though, just in case that part is somehow actually in the middle of the ship.

Awesome, that did it. Docked with 6 whole units of monoprop left. Probably now don't have enough to dock with the mpl I came to dock with, but we'll see.

10 hours ago, Geonovast said:

You could probably blow it up by using the object thrower in the F12 cheat menu.

Save first, though, just in case that part is somehow actually in the middle of the ship.

So is there something I did wrong building this ship that I can avoid in the future? Is it possible it's because the stage that had the reaction wheel was an MPL which couldn't control it without the command module, so when I jettisoned the MPL it left the reaction wheel with the command module that was using it?

24 minutes ago, Kchinger said:

So is there something I did wrong building this ship that I can avoid in the future? Is it possible it's because the stage that had the reaction wheel was an MPL which couldn't control it without the command module, so when I jettisoned the MPL it left the reaction wheel with the command module that was using it? 

I doubt it.  Unless you built them together in the VAB and somehow offset the reaction wheel to the other side of the docking ports.  This is definitely some kind of weird bug, which I experienced something similar recently.  Although I attributed it to the mod Konstruction getting confused during welding.  Do you still have the original craft file where the MPL was attached?
